Detecting Personality and Mental Disorders Through Monitoring Computer Usage

Hypothesis: Personality and mental disorders show patterns in the way a person uses a computer.

Methods:
Use Markov chains to categorize computer actions.
Ex: Find a sequence of actions performed that happen repeatedly.
Ritualistic behavior may be reflected in this.

Categorize computer programs
Detect when programs are switched into focus
Measure speed of mouse movements, button clicked, and programs switched

